File: The department is encouraging farmers to take precautionary measures. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng authorities are warning farmers of a new outbreak of African swine fever. The latest flare-up was detected in the Swaniesville area. This is the third time the disease has been found this year. READ: Pork consumers warned to cook food well In April, Daveyton informal pig farmers reported the unusual deaths of pigs brought in from Mpumalanga. More outbreaks were reported in May, in Vanderbijlpark. The department is encouraging farmers to take precautionary measures. This includes not feeding pigs leftover food and not buying pigs of unknown origin.